{
  "name": "thumbgrove",
  "description": "A warm kalimba grove at golden hour, woody tines buzzing softly like cicadas at peace. Plucked metal tines on a wooden gourd — warm and earthy with a gentle characteristic buzz that decays fast — over a low gourd-resonated bass heartbeat. Two interlocking lead tines weave a hypnotic mbira cross-rhythm, answered by a sweet muted tone, a bright shimmering chime, scattered seed-pod sparkles, a bowed-gourd bloom, a hocketed thumb-pluck cluster, a dry calabash knuckle tap, and a happy buzzing chirp up top. A major pentatonic @ A=432, additive and clean, African-sunlit and joyful — hypnotic, never harsh, never dreary.",
